olive oil
3 potato
1 Brown Onion
1 packet pulled chicken
1 sachet All-American Spice Blend
1 packet BBQ sauce
20 g butter
1 bag Slaw Mix
1 packet mayonnaise
1 packet Smoked Cheddar Cheese
1 bag coriander

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut potato into fries.
• Place fries on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat.
• Spread out evenly, then bake until tender, 20-25 minutes.

• When the fries have 10 minutes remaining, thinly slice onion.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook onion until tender, 3-4 minutes.
• Cook pulled chicken and All-American spice blend, breaking up with a spoon, until browned, 2-3 minutes.
• Add BBQ sauce, the butter and a splash of water, stirring, until well combined, 1 minute.

• In a large bowl, combine slaw mix and mayonnaise. Season to taste.

• Divide potato fries between plates.
• Top with American BBQ pulled chicken and sprinkle over smoked Cheddar cheese.
• Serve with slaw and tear over coriander. Enjoy!